Singularity Systems: Zero to Hero (The Hacker's Guide to Tensor Compilers)
(by j4orz)

------------------
Course Description
------------------
Singularity Systems bridges the missing gap in the ecosystem for low level system
programmers and performance engineers interested in the internals of deep learning
frameworks. The course provides the software 2.0 equivalent of SICP (interpreters)
and the dragon book (compilers), where you will build an interpreter along the
lines of PyTorch 1.0 and a compiler along the lines of PyTorch 2.0, line by line
from scratch. By the end of Singularity Systems, you will be better equipped to
contribute towards opensource projects such as pytorch and jax, both ~100kLOC.

Prereqs
-------
- solid deep learning (gpt2 && llama2 && r1)
- solid systems programming (C || C++ || Rust || Python*)

  *: python is ok (following the footsteps of pure-python systems such as
     PyTorch 2.0 and CUTLASS 4.0), as long as you're coming in with basic
     computer architecture fundamentals.

Syllabus
--------
  0. au197
  1. dfdx(nd)
  2. brrr
  3. pt2
  4. cloud
  ---Appendix
  A. nets
  B. ctorisc

Citation
--------
j4orz (2025) Singularity Systems. https://github.com/j4orz/singularitysystems
OR
